import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['Date'] = pd.to_datetime(data['Date'], errors='coerce')
    data = data[pd.notna(data['Date'])]

    plt.figure(figsize=(12, 6))
    sns.lineplot(x='Date', y='CO2', data=data, label='CO2 Concentration')
    plt.title('What is the trend of CO2 concentration over time?', wrap=True)
    plt.xlabel('Date')
    plt.ylabel('CO2 Concentration')
    plt.legend()
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    sns.histplot(data=data, x='CO2', kde=True, color='blue', label='CO2 concentration')
    plt.axvline(data['CO2'].median(), color='red', linestyle='--', label=f"Median: {data['CO2'].median():.2f}")
    plt.title('What is the distribution of CO2 concentration?', wrap=True)
    plt.legend()
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['Date'] = pd.to_datetime(data['Date'], errors='coerce')
    data = data[pd.notna(data['Date'])]

    plt.figure(figsize=(10, 6))
    sns.scatterplot(x='CO2', y='adjusted_CO2', data=data)
    plt.title('What is the relationship between CO2 and adjusted CO2 concentration?', wrap=True)
    plt.xlabel('CO2 Concentration')
    plt.ylabel('Adjusted CO2 Concentration')
    plt.legend(title='CO2 vs Adjusted CO2', loc='upper left')

    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['Date'] = pd.to_datetime(data['Date'], errors='coerce')
    data = data[pd.notna(data['Date'])]
    data['Year'] = data['Date'].dt.year
    yearly_avg = data.groupby('Year')['CO2'].mean().reset_index()

    plt.figure(figsize=(12, 6))
    sns.barplot(x='Year', y='CO2', data=yearly_avg, palette='viridis')
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    plt.title('What is the average CO2 concentration over the years?', wrap=True)
    plt.xlabel('Year')
    plt.ylabel('Average CO2 Concentration')
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
